'''Largest Human Flag of India''' was an event organised to form the world's largest human national flag in Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India. It was organised on 7 December 2014 by Rotary International in India with a slogan '''Rotary My Flag My India'''. More than 50,000 Indians gathered in YMCA Grounds, [[Chennai]] to form the world's largest human national flag.<ref>{{cite web|author=Tuesday, Dec 09, 2014 |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141207/nation-current-affairs/article/india-set-new-world-record-largest-human-flag |title=India set new world record for largest human flag |publisher=Deccanchronicle.com |date= |accessdate=2014-12-09}}</ref>
It is the official attempt to break the previous world record was in the name of Sports Club of Lahore, [[Pakistan]]. They made their national flag by gathering 28,957 human on February 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/30000-chennaiites-break-record-with-human-tricolour/article6670936.ece |title=Together, they fly Guinness flag |publisher=The Hindu |date= |accessdate=2014-12-09}}</ref>
Guinness official Syeda Subasi-Gemici, adjudicator of [[Guinness World Records]] Ltd., presented the certificate validating the attempt.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/india/india-set-new-world-record-for-largest-human-flag-beating-pakistan_1511002.html |title=India set new world record for largest human flag, beating Pakistan &#124; Zee News |publisher=Zeenews.india.com |date= |accessdate=2014-12-09}}</ref>
