{{distinguish|Kháng language}} {{Infobox language |name=Tay Khang |nativename= |states=[[Laos]] |speakers=1,500 |date=1999 |ref=Schliesinger 2003 |familycolor=Tai–Kadai |fam1=[[Kra–Dai languages|Kra–Dai]] |fam2=[[Tai languages|Tai]] |fam3=[[Southwestern Tai languages|Southwestern]]? |lc1=tnu|ld1=Tay Khang |glotto=tayk1238 |glottorefname=Tay Khang }}
'''Tay Khang''', or just '''Kang''', is a [[Tai languages|Tai language]] of Laos. There is confusion with [[Kháng language|Kháng]]. Schliesinger (2003) reports an area of habitation being Bolikhamsai proviences in Laos.
Religion of speakers is Theravada Buddhism and animism.
An audio recording in this language by Michel Ferlus is available online from the [[Pangloss Collection]].[http://lacito.vjf.cnrs.fr/pangloss/corpus/show_text.php?id=crdo-TNU_TAYKHANG_SOUND]
